[375-dates]
LEVEL=run
JQ = {{{
[strptime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ")|(.,mktime)]
}}}
INPUT = {{{
"2015-03-05T23:51:47Z"
}}}
EXPECTED = {{{
[[2015,2,5,23,51,47,4,63],1425599507]
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$pyrun=t = __import__('time').strptime(_, '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ')\narr = [t.tm_year, t.tm_mon - 1, t.tm_mday, t.tm_hour, t.tm_min, t.tm_sec, (t.tm_wday + 1) % 7, t.tm_yday - 1]\nts = __import__('calendar').timegm(t)\nreturn [arr, ts]"}
}}}
COMMENT=strptime (string -> broken-down array) is the reverse of gmtime's conversion, plus a mktime-equivalent from the same parsed struct — binding "t" once via run tier avoids re-parsing the string 8+ times.
